raw_data.title: Managing Consultant
raw_data.description: The Managing Consultant will directly manage all aspects of a set of client projects providing overall leadership.  He will provide administrative management for a project staff of up to 10-20 people on various projects including project staff time,  expense (T&E) approvals and project performance evaluations.  The Managing Consultant has the primary responsibility for ensuring overall client project satisfaction and managing client expectations.  The Managing Consultant oversees the completion of customer solutions and strategies based on the analysis of the customer’s business goals, objectives, needs and general business environment.  The Managing Consultant provides both management and technical leadership and is an expert at using project management tools to estimate projects and monitor their status.  Receives assignments in the form of objectives and defines goals and activities required to meet objectives.  Provides guidance to team to achieve goals in accordance with established policies.  The Management Consultant oversees and is responsible for the completion and quality of functional specifications, design, system and technical architecture definition, development, implementation, unit and system testing.  The Management Consultant recommends changes to policies that affect overall consulting operations.

raw_data.title: Senior Practice Manager
raw_data.description: The Practice Manager directs highly specialized phases of system analysis, design, and implementation.  This position leads a team of engineers or consultants through the investigation of technical issues in the customer’s environment and functions as the technical expert during product presentations to the client.  He or she possesses industry leading expertise in a technology Practice such as networking, electronic business or software applications, and is able to provide consultative technical support at high levels of the enterprise.   The Practice Manager analyzes the environment, business goals and objectives and applies leading edge technology in a specific Practice to the client environment.  The position directs the team through troubleshooting and identification of high-level, complex technical problems, while ensuring overall design and implementation follows current technology solutions that are aligned to the Practice for enterprise customers.
